  "datePublished": "2026-03-31",
  "description": "When the source of threat is structural, the nervous system's defensive response initiates but cannot complete, producing chronic activation that becomes invisible through sensory-motor amnesia. Five traditions describe this single pathway from structural crisis to managed bodily activation.",
